    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe problem is described in the title.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n`nvim --clean -c \"set completeopt+=fuzzy\"`\nThen insert some indented texts and use `<C-X><C-L>` to reproduce.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe leading spaces in the completion items are trimmed correctly.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.13.0-dev-628+gedcaf1887a\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes, vim 9.2.0573\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux 7.0.10\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkonsole 26.04.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
